column2:
By now, we all know that Amber Heard is a proven liar (there's no time to get into all of that; look it up for yourself if you want details), so removing her from Aquaman 2 would benefit the movie as well as society. And the good news is that she is getting removed. 
But doing all of that was the easy part. The real question now is: Who will replace her? I have my answer, and it's Lily-Rose Depp. 
Think of it as the Ultimate Middle-Finger to Amber after everything Lily has been through, because as far as I'm concerned, she (Lily) was patient-zero of the Johnny vs. Amber debacle. 
Emilia Clarke has also been considered, and she would be a solid choice too, but she's a very-close second. I have nothing against Emilia in general, but Lily deserves this more than anyone. Especially given recent events.
